Well I have fvwm 2.0.47b running ok with Solaris 2.5 and X11R6.3.
The one problem I noticed is that the build did not set the LD_RUN_PATH.
It may be an issue with the Imakefile of my site.def file. I need to check
on this still. Anyone else have this problem? This is a shared library issue
where you need to tell the compiler at build time where to look for the
libraries at run time.

I have included a small patch (which defaults to False). It puts
"StipledTitles" in all window titles. This is the default behaviour for our
1000+ Unix boxes and 50,000 user base. It would save me alot of hassle if
you could incorporate it in 2.0.47, as it is small and does not effect
normal behavior.

Thanks,
Randall

--- 1.1	1998/06/23 22:20:38
+++ borders.c	1998/06/23 22:21:30
@@ -848,7 +848,7 @@
                      t->name, strlen(t->name));
   }
   /* now, draw lines in title bar if it's a sticky window */
-  if(t->flags & STICKY)
+  if(t->flags & STICKY || Scr.StipledTitles)
   {
     for(i=0 ;i< t->title_height/2-3;i+=4)
     {
--- 1.1	1998/06/23 22:22:17
+++ builtins.c	1998/06/23 22:24:11
@@ -3323,6 +3323,14 @@
     {
       Scr.MouseFocusClickRaises = True;
     }
+    else if (StrEquals(opt,"NOSTIPLEDTITLES"))
+    {
+      Scr.StipledTitles = False;
+    }
+    else if (StrEquals(opt,"STIPLEDTITLES"))
+    {
+      Scr.StipledTitles = True;
+    }
     else
       fvwm_msg(ERR,"GlobalOpts","Unknown Global Option '%s'",opt);
 
--- 1.1	1998/06/23 22:24:30
+++ fvwm.c	1998/06/23 22:25:20
@@ -1242,6 +1242,7 @@
   Scr.ClickToFocusPassesClick = True;
   Scr.ClickToFocusRaises = True;
   Scr.MouseFocusClickRaises = False;
+  Scr.StipledTitles = False;
 
   /* Not the right place for this, should only be called once somewhere .. */
   InitPictureCMap(dpy,Scr.Root);
--- 1.1	1998/06/23 22:25:30
+++ screen.h	1998/06/23 22:25:46
@@ -332,6 +332,7 @@
   int ClickToFocusPassesClick;
   int ClickToFocusRaises;
   int MouseFocusClickRaises;
+  int StipledTitles;
 
 } ScreenInfo;
 
--- 1.1	1998/06/23 22:26:18
+++ fvwm2.man	1998/06/23 22:26:38
@@ -1112,6 +1112,7 @@
 ClickToFocusDoesntPassClick/ClickToFocusPassesClick,
 ClickToFocusDoesntRaise/ClickToFocusRaises,
 MouseFocusClickDoesntRaise/MouseFocusClickRaises
+NoStipledTitles/StipledTitles
 .EX
 GlobalOpts ClickToFocusDoesntPassClick, ClickToFocusDoesntRaise
 .EE

