fvwm under solaris should compile with the /usr/openwin/ X11 installation.
Unfortunately the Imake support under solaris was broken until 2.6

the problem is described on
http://night.primate.wisc.edu/software/imake-stuff/imake-vs-openwin.html
there you can also find patches to fix the problem ... 

about shared libraries ... 

the LD_RUN_PATH variable must be set or every -L on the compiler commandline
should be accompanied by a -R pointing to the same place as the -L ...
otherwhise the solaris shared library loader will not find the X libraries
or any other library no located in /usr/lib ...

cheers
tobi

