I'll look into this, but probably not until Friday.  The main
motivations for the menu changes were:

1) Provide reasonable keyboard-based behaviour;  the old menus were
abysmally bad at managing menus with keystrokes (right-arrow moved the
pointer over some fixed number of pixels, instead of doing something
conceptually appropriate, etc.)

2) Deal better with the "out-of-space-at-right-side-of-screen" problem; 
animating top level windows out of the way turned out to be a pretty
nifty effect (on a reasonably fast server) and seems like the right thing

3) Generalize the code to handle deep menus; the old code only handled
depths of up to 3, because static variables were used to hold, e.g., the 
prior menu and the one before that.

The code is not trivial, but neither was the old code.  The new menuing
code isn't a few features chucked into crap, it's rewritten from first
principles, twice!  (My machine crashed after the first rewrite, before
my weekly backup, so I had to redo everything---better!)

I'll look into your patch and see if I can figure out what's the reason
for the different behaviour -- I've not looked at the code in a while,
and my rewrite for SCWM is pretty different, unfortunately (we were
shooting for more flexibility, there, though it still doesn't have
animated menus).

Greg
