Build comments:


-)  Fvwm.tmpl
    #define HasXpm  YES     /* NO */
                  ^^

    two whitespaces !!!
    this has produced severe problems in the past (some old compilers don't cut
    spaces)

    It's no problem for me any more.


-)  I still had to 

    xmkmf; make all; make install; make install.man
           ^^^^^^^^
    otherwise the lib isn't built, thus all other targets fail.

    I think the 'install' target should build the library.

-)  unluckily there's not much use in using make -j -l2.5 (parallel make)
    because of the batch-character of the main makefile (imake).

    I tried an aggressive make (all on one line):
	
	make clean ; xmkmf ; nice make -j -l2 Makefiles ; 
        nice make -j -l2 all install install.man 

    resulting in several .c files being compiled twice.
    (more precise: in parallel:
	the toplevel Makefile has independent rules for 'all' and 'install'
	so 2 different makes are executed in each directory in parallel.)

	> nice make -j -l2 -n all install install | egrep '\.\.\.$'
	making all in ./libs...
	installing in ./libs...
	installing in ./fvwm...		(but dependent of 'all' -> make 'all' first)
	making all in ./fvwm...		(this competes with the above process)
	installing in ./modules/FvwmAudio...
	making all in ./modules/FvwmAudio...
	... and so on.


	the individual makefiles (except the 'libs' one) _have_ 'install'
	depending on 'all', so there's 2 makes taking care of 'all'.


    so one safe way is:	
	make clean ; xmkmf ; nice make -j -l2 Makefiles ; 
	nice make -j -l2 -C libs ; nice make -j -l2 install ;
	nice make -j -l2 install.man 

	(note that the library has to be taken care of separately, 
	because 'install' doesn't build the lib.)

   or :
	make clean ; xmkmf ; nice make -j -l2 Makefiles ; 
	nice make -j -l2 all ; nice make -j -l2 install install.man

   anyway: you almost can't use parallel make to make fvwm2.

   usually the load is at 0.22 for normal make over NFS (the net is
   sometimes the limiting factor).

   ----- want to say: the make process still needs work & optimizations.



