I have run into a problem with fvwm2.0.47b right from the start.

My problem is that when the window manager starts, my FvwmButtons starts at a
different geometry location then I specified in the file.

I use a separate config file for Fvwmbuttons.  I have the following in my "rc"
file:

*FvwmButtonsFile /home/misha21/.fvwm2.0.47/buttons/fvwmbuttons

and this is the line in that file for the geometry:

Geometry +1228+133

Instead of the above location, Fvwmbuttons start at +1264+327.

When I execute a re-start of fvwm2 it moves FvwmButtons to +1264+327.

What could cause this behavior?

I have compiled fvwm2.0.47b with gcc version 2.8.0, x11r6.1 under Solaris 2.5.1
with the works.

The only other problem I noticed is one that has already been mentioned.  My
default menus will not stay up with just a click of the mouse over the desktop. 
I have to hold the mouse down, sweep across the box and then the menus will stay
up.

My previous version of fvwm2 is fvwm2.0.45, and I have not had any of these
