This is a patch for Fvwm.tmpl that takes care of the "shared library" issue
for my Solaris machines. I turned it in last week but did not hear any
comments back on it.

I have successfully built fvwm-2.0.47b with this patch on the following
platforms and various releases of X11R6.

alpha_dux40 hp700_ux90 rs_aix42 sgi_62 sun4m_55 sun4m_56


The patch basically changes;
$(CC) -o $@ $(OBJS) $(LDOPTIONS).......

to

$(CCENVSETUP) $(CC) -o $@ $(OBJS) $(LDOPTIONS).....


I do not think this will cause anyone else a problem but would be interested
to hear if it did.

CCENVSETUP is defined in the X11 config tree.

If it does not cause a problem, it should probably be included.

Thanks,
Randall

